    SingularIntegralEquations.Directed ‚Äî Type.

    Directed represents a number that is a limit from either left (s=true) or right (s=false) For functions with branch cuts, it is assumed that the value is on the branch cut, Therefore not requiring tolerances. This will naturally give the analytic continuation.
